Riemann 问题
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "subsec:RiemannProblems"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset nomenclature
LatexCommand nomenclature
symbol "RP"
description "Riemann Problem"
literal "false"

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Without loss of generality, we shall only discuss Riemann problems in 1D
 space and shift the initial discontinuity to 
\begin_inset Formula $(x_{0},t_{0})=(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

[RP for Single Conservation Law]
\end_layout

\end_inset

The Riemann problem
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for a single conservation law
\end_layout

\end_inset

 for a single conservation law in 1D space is the IVP defined by PDE 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ConservationLaw1dScalar"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and the following IC:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t=0)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x<0\\
U_{+} & x>0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

in which 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{+}$
\end_inset

 are two constants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Problem
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

[RP for Conservation Law System]
\end_layout

\end_inset

The Riemann problem for a system of conservation laws
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for a conservation law system
\end_layout

\end_inset

 in 1D space is the IVP defined by PDE 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:ConservationLaws1dSystem"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 and the following IC:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\ket{U(x,t=0)}=\begin{cases}
\ket{U_{-}} & x<0\\
\ket{U_{+}} & x>0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

in which, 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U_{-}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U_{+}}$
\end_inset

 are two constant column matrices.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark*
The value of 
\begin_inset Formula $U$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

 is mathematically undefined, which does not affect the solution obtained
 in the following sections, but may cause unpleasant results when implemented
 in computer programs.
 To remove such pitfall, we shall use the mean value of 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{+}$
\end_inset

 for 
\begin_inset Formula $U(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

