\begin_layout Subsection
线性单波方程
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
PDE!linear advection equation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for linear advection equation
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Solution*
线性单波方程的通量为
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
F(U)=\lambda U\qquad\lambda\in\mathbb{R}
\]

\end_inset

它的 Riemann 问题的解为
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<\lambda\\
U_{+} & x/t>\lambda
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

这个解在特征线 
\begin_inset Formula $x/t=\lambda$
\end_inset

 上不满足 PDE，但满足跳跃关系及（退化的）熵条件：
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u^{\Gamma}=\frac{F_{+}-F_{-}}{U_{+}-U_{-}}=\lambda\qquad\lambda(U_{-})=u^{\Gamma}=\lambda(U_{+})
\]

\end_inset

因此是这种间断是接触间断
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!contact ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
线性多波方程组
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for a linear hyperbolic system
\end_layout

\end_inset

Like in the smooth case, the first step is to project the IC onto the space
 spanned by 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \ket{R_{i}}\right\} _{i=1}^{m}$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\ket{U_{-}}=\sum_{i=1}^{m}\ket{R_{i}}\ip{L_{i}}{U_{-}}\qquad\ket{U_{+}}=\sum_{i=1}^{m}\ket{R_{i}}\ip{L_{i}}{U_{+}}
\]

\end_inset

The IVP then becomes 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 independent RPs for linear wave equations:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\pdv{v_{i}}{t}+\lambda_{i}\pdv{v_{i}}{x}=0\qquad v_{i}(x,t=0)=\ip{i}{V(x,t=0)}=\begin{cases}
\ip{L_{i}}{U_{-}} & x<0\\
\ip{L_{i}}{U_{+}} & x>0
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

We know their solutions are:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
v_{i}(x,t)=\ip{i}{V(x,t)}=\begin{cases}
\ip{L_{i}}{U_{-}} & x/t<\lambda_{i}\\
\ip{L_{i}}{U_{+}} & x/t>\lambda_{i}
\end{cases}\qquad i=1,\dots,m
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The solution of the original RP is then the 
\emph on
superposition
\emph default
 of all the 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 independent waves carrying the initial jump.
 Note that the 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

th wave propagates with speed 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{i}$
\end_inset

, so the 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,t)$
\end_inset

 plane is divided into 
\begin_inset Formula $(m+1)$
\end_inset

 regions by the 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 straight characteristic curves emanating from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th region where
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{k}<x/t<\lambda_{k+1}\qquad k=1,\dots,m-1
\]

\end_inset

we know that
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the jumps in the first 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 waves are to the 
\emph on
left
\emph default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,t)$
\end_inset

, so these waves contributes their 
\emph on
right
\emph default
 values;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the jumps in the other 
\begin_inset Formula $(m-k)$
\end_inset

 waves are to the 
\emph on
right
\emph default
 of 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,t)$
\end_inset

, so these waves contributes their 
\emph on
left
\emph default
 values;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
the value of 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U}$
\end_inset

 at 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,t)$
\end_inset

 (except for those locate on the discontinuities) is the superposition of
 them:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\ket{U(x,t)} & =\sum_{i=1}^{k}\ip{L_{i}}{U_{+}}\ket{R_{i}}+\sum_{i=k+1}^{m}\ip{L_{i}}{U_{-}}\ket{R_{i}}\\
\ket{F(x,t)} & =\sum_{i=1}^{k}\ip{L_{i}}{U_{+}}\lambda_{i}\ket{R_{i}}+\sum_{i=k+1}^{m}\ip{L_{i}}{U_{-}}\lambda_{i}\ket{R_{i}}
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

which is similar to the smooth case.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

th region where 
\begin_inset Formula $x/t<\lambda_{1}$
\end_inset

 and the 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

th region where 
\begin_inset Formula $x/t>\lambda_{m}$
\end_inset

, none of the single waves arrive, so 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U(x,t)}=\ket{U_{-}}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U_{+}}$
\end_inset

 respectively.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\ket{U(x,t)}=\begin{cases}
\ket{U_{-}} & x/t<\lambda_{1}\\
\ket{U_{*}} & x/t\in(\lambda_{k},\lambda_{k+1})\\
\ket{U_{+}} & x/t>\lambda_{m}
\end{cases}\qc k=1,\dots,m-1
\]

\end_inset

where
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\ket{U_{*}}=\left(\sum_{i=1}^{k}\dyad{R_{i}}{L_{i}}\right)\ket{U_{+}}+\left(\sum_{i=k+1}^{m}\dyad{R_{i}}{L_{i}}\right)\ket{U_{-}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark*
For each 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

, the PDE is not satisfied on the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th characteristic curve 
\begin_inset Formula $x/t=\lambda_{k}=u^{\Gamma_{k}}$
\end_inset

.
 Instead, the jump condition
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\eval{\ket{U(x,t)}}_{k-}^{k+}u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\eval{\ket{F(x,t)}}_{k-}^{k+}
\]

\end_inset

and the entropy condition
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{k-1}(\lambda_{k}t-0,t)<\lambda_{k}(\lambda_{k}t-0,t)=u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\lambda_{k}(\lambda_{k}t+0,t)<\lambda_{k+1}(\lambda_{k}t+0,t)
\]

\end_inset

are satisfied, in which
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\begin{aligned}\eval{\ket{U(x,t)}}_{k-}^{k+} & =\ket{U(\lambda_{k}t+0,t)}-\ket{U(\lambda_{k}t-0,t)}=\dyad{R_{k}}{L_{k}}\big(\ket{U_{+}}-\ket{U_{-}}\big)\\
\eval{\ket{F(x,t)}}_{k-}^{k+} & =\ket{F(\lambda_{k}t+0,t)}-\ket{F(\lambda_{k}t-0,t)}=\lambda_{k}\dyad{R_{k}}{L_{k}}\big(\ket{U_{+}}-\ket{U_{-}}\big)
\end{aligned}
\]

\end_inset

They are all contact discontinuities.
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!contact ~
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
拟线性单波方程
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for a single conservation law
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The disturbance of the initial discontinuity spreads at a finite speed,
 so there must be two undisturbed regions in the solution, in which 
\begin_inset Formula $U(x,t)$
\end_inset

 takes its initial value.
 These two undisturbed regions are connected by a disturbed region.
 Self-similarity implies that the interfaces of these regions are straight
 lines emanated from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
 So, the solution must have the following form:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<\lambda_{-}\\
U_{*} & x/t\in[\lambda_{-},\lambda_{+}]\\
U_{+} & x/t>\lambda_{+}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

in which
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda(U)=\pdv{F}{U}\qquad\lambda_{\pm}=\lambda(U_{\pm})
\]

\end_inset

Our task is to determine 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{*}$
\end_inset

, which is a function depends on 
\begin_inset Formula $x/t$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
激波 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!shock wave
\end_layout

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}>U_{+}$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}<0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}<U_{+}$
\end_inset

, we will have 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}>\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, which means the characteristic curves emanating from one half of the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

-axis will 
\emph on
run into
\emph default
 those emanating from the other half of the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

-axis.
 In this case, a 
\noun on
shock wave
\noun default
 separating the two families of parallel characteristic curves will emanate
 from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
 The speed of the shock wave is determined by the jump condition and the
 entropy condition
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u^{\Gamma}=\frac{F_{+}-F_{-}}{U_{+}-U_{-}}\qquad\lambda_{-}>u^{\Gamma}>\lambda_{+}
\]

\end_inset

is strictly satisfied.
 The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<u^{\Gamma}\\
\text{shock} & x/t=u^{\Gamma}\\
U_{+} & x/t>u^{\Gamma}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
膨胀波 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}<U_{+}$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}<0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}>U_{+}$
\end_inset

, we will have 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}<\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, which means the two families of characteristic curves will 
\emph on
diverge
\emph default
 from each other.
 In this case, a fan-shaped 
\noun on
centered expansion wave
\noun default
 separating the two families of parallel characteristic curves will start
 from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
 The speed of the 
\noun on
wave head
\noun default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, while that of the 
\noun on
wave tail
\noun default
 is 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}$
\end_inset

.
 In the region between them, 
\begin_inset Formula $u(x,t)$
\end_inset

 is smooth enough to satisfy the PDE, which can be solved from the equation
 of characteristic curves:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u(x,t)=\lambda^{-1}(x/t)\impliedby x/t=\lambda(u)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda^{-1}$
\end_inset

 means the inverse function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

.
 The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<\lambda_{-}\\
\text{expansion} & x/t\in\left[\lambda_{-},\lambda_{+}\right]\\
U_{+} & x/t>\lambda_{+}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
接触间断 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!contact ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

There might be such a case that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}=\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, even though 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}\ne U_{+}$
\end_inset

.
 In this case, there will be no mass/momentum/energy flowing across the
 discontinuity, thus it is called a 
\noun on
contact discontinuity
\noun default
.
 The speed of the contact discontinuity is the same as the left and right
 characteristic speed:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{-}=u^{\Gamma}=\lambda_{+}
\]

\end_inset

The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<u^{\Gamma}\\
\text{contact} & x/t=u^{\Gamma}\\
U_{+} & x/t>u^{\Gamma}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

接触间断兼具激波与膨胀波的特性：
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
A contact discontinuity can be seen as a limit case of a shock wave, since
 it is indeed a discontinuity, across which, the jump condition and the
 entropy condition are satisfied.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
A contact discontinuity can also be seen as a limit case of a centered expansion
 wave, when the angle of the fan-shaped region shrinks to 
\begin_inset Formula $0^{\circ}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
一般守恒律方程组
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for a conservation law system
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Lemma
守恒律方程组的 Riemann 解具有自相似结构：
\begin_inset Formula $(x,t)$
\end_inset

 平面被 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 个基本波（激波、膨胀波、接触间断）划分为 
\begin_inset Formula $(m+1)$
\end_inset

 个扇形常值区域。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
There are 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 characteristic fields, so the initial discontinuity will be carried by
 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 elementary waves.
 Since the solution of an RP is self-similar, we can define the 
\noun on
slope
\noun default
 as a new independent variable:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha:=x/t\implies\begin{cases}
\pdv*{t}=(\pdv*{\alpha}{t})(\dv*{\alpha})\\
\pdv*{x}=(\pdv*{\alpha}{x})(\dv*{\alpha})
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

PDE 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:multi_wave_quasilinear_system"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 can be transformed into
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\Matrix{A}-\alpha\Matrix{I}\right)\ket{\dv{U}{\alpha}}=\ket{0}
\]

\end_inset

which implies in smooth regions, either 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{\dv*{U}{\alpha}}=\ket{0}$
\end_inset

, which means 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U}$
\end_inset

 is constant, or 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 is an eigenvalue of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Matrix{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{\dv*{U}{\alpha}}$
\end_inset

 is the corresponding right eigenvector.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Notation
Denote the slope on the right and left side of 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th elementary wave as 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}$
\end_inset

 respectively.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}=\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 cannot imply 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U(\alpha_{k-})}=\ket{U(\alpha_{k+})}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For shock waves, there are there 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}=\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For centered expansion waves, there are 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}<\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k\pm})=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For contact discontinuities, there are there 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}=\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k\pm})=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Lemma
激波或膨胀波一定属于真正非线性的特征场，接触间断一定属于线性退化的特征场。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
激波 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!shock wave
\end_layout

\end_inset

If the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th characteristic field is genuinely nonlinear, there might be such a case
 that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k-})>\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k+})
\]

\end_inset

Geometrically, this means the characteristic curves on both sides run 
\emph on
into
\emph default
 each other, which implies 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th elementary wave is a shock wave.
 Physically, there are mass/momentum/energy flowing across the wave with
 entropy increasing.
 The change of 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{F}$
\end_inset

 must satisfy the jump condition:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\eval{\ket{U}}_{k-}^{k+}u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\eval{\ket{F}}_{k-}^{k+}
\]

\end_inset

in which 
\begin_inset Formula $u^{\Gamma_{k}}$
\end_inset

 is the speed of the shock wave, which is also the slope of the shock wave
 path, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
 The entropy condition is satisfied with strict unequal signs:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k-})>u^{\Gamma_{k}}>\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k+})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
膨胀波 If the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th characteristic field is genuinely nonlinear, there might be such a case
 that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{k-1}(\alpha_{k-})<\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k-})<\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k+})<\lambda_{k+1}(\alpha_{k+})
\]

\end_inset

Geometrically, this means the characteristic curves on both sides wave run
 
\emph on
away
\emph default
 from each other, which implies 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th elementary wave is a centered expansion wave.
 Inside the wave, the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

-characteristic curves must diverse from each other:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dv{\lambda_{k}(\alpha)}{\alpha}\ge0\qquad\alpha\in[\lambda_{-},\lambda_{+}]
\]

\end_inset

in which
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{-}=\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k-})=\alpha_{k-}\qquad\lambda_{+}=\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k+})=\alpha_{k+}
\]

\end_inset

are the speed of the wave head and the wave tail, respectively.
 A centered expansion wave is a smooth region, in which 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha:=x/t$
\end_inset

 is an eigenvalue of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Matrix{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{\dv*{U}{\alpha}}$
\end_inset

 is the corresponding right eigenvector.
 So, the 
\begin_inset Formula $(m-1)$
\end_inset

 generalized 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

-Riemann invariants are constants across wave:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dv{\phi}{\alpha}=\ip{\grad{\phi}}{\dv{U}{\alpha}}=\ip{\grad{\phi}}{R_{k}}=0
\]

\end_inset

which can be used to determine state inside the wave:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi(\alpha_{k-})=\phi(\alpha)=\phi(\alpha_{k+})\qquad\alpha\in[\alpha_{k-},\alpha_{k+}]
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
接触间断 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!contact ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

If the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th characteristic field is linearly degenerate, then 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{k}$
\end_inset

 does not change with 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U}$
\end_inset

, which implies
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{k-1}(\alpha_{k-})<\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k-})=\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k+})<\lambda_{k+1}(\alpha_{k+})
\]

\end_inset

Geometrically, this means the characteristic curves on both sides run 
\emph on
parallel
\emph default
 with each other, which implies 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th elementary wave is a contact discontinuity.
 Physically, there is no mass/momentum/energy flowing across a contact discontin
uity, thus no entropy increasing.
 The jump condition and the entropy condition are satisfied automatically.
 A contact discontinuity can also be seen as a limit case of a centered
 expansion wave, when the angle of the fan-shaped region tends to be 
\begin_inset Formula $0$
\end_inset

.
 So, the 
\begin_inset Formula $(m-1)$
\end_inset

 generalized 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

-Riemann invariants are constants across the wave:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dv{\phi}{\alpha}=\ip{\grad{\phi}}{\dv{U}{\alpha}}=\ip{\grad{\phi}}{R_{k}}=0
\]

\end_inset

which can be used to connect states on both sides of the wave:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\phi(\alpha_{k-})=\phi(\alpha_{k+})
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

